<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,150,321]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,368,186,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">Identification.</emphasis>
This species was identified from descriptions and illustrations found in the revision by 
<bibRefCitation author="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Blahnik, R. J." pageId="3" pageNumber="581" pagination="1 - 37" refId="ref5850" refString="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Blahnik, R. J. (2006) The caddisfly genus Protoptila in Costa Rica (Trichoptera: Glossosomatidae). Zootaxa, 1197, 1 - 37." type="journal article" year="2006">Holzenthal &amp; Blahnik (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. The horn-like processes projecting from the phallicata are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Holzenthal &amp; Blahnik 2006" authorityName="Holzenthal &amp; Blahnik" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Glossosomatidae" genus="Protoptila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristula">
<emphasis box="[1197,1309,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">P. cristula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Blahnik, R. J." pageId="3" pageNumber="581" pagination="1 - 37" refId="ref5850" refString="Holzenthal, R. W. &amp; Blahnik, R. J. (2006) The caddisfly genus Protoptila in Costa Rica (Trichoptera: Glossosomatidae). Zootaxa, 1197, 1 - 37." type="journal article" year="2006">Holzenthal &amp; Blahnik 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mosely 1937" authorityName="Mosely" authorityYear="1937" box="[388,620,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Glossosomatidae" genus="Protoptila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rota">
<emphasis box="[388,463,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="581">P. rota</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mosely, M. E." box="[470,620,259,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="581" pagination="151 - 190" refId="ref6306" refString="Mosely, M. E. (1937) Mexican Hydroptilidae (Trichoptera). Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 86 (10), 151 - 190. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1937. tb 00242. x" type="journal article" year="1937">Mosely 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from these two species by the shorter, ventral processes of the phallicata and by the ventral margin of sternum VIII, which is shorter and less deeply bifurcate apically.
</paragraph>
